java.lang.Object
  grails-app.domain.org.raap.domain.Client

class Client

The Client class represents a person who receives services from RAAP. Clients are at the heart of the Client Services domain model.

static def fsm_def
Change the state of this Client record. This mimics the workflow behavior that the FSM plugin is *meant* to support but I cannot seem to get the unit tests to work.
param:
newState String fire_state(newState) { def oldState = this.state switch ( this.state ) { case 'PreIntake': switch ( newState ) { case 'PreIntake': println "Stay in PreIntake" // log.debug "Stay in PreIntake" break case 'Evaluation': println "Move to Evaluation" // log.debug "Move to Evaluation" this.state = 'Evaluation' break } break case 'Evaluation': switch ( newState ) { case 'PreIntake': def message = "Cannot go back to the PreIntake state"; println message throw new RuntimeException(message); break case 'Evaluation': println "Staty in Evaluation" break } break } return oldState }
